table_trans: The promotion has been granted in the public interest as an administrative urgency to the posts lying vacant due to the move of officers of the Under Secretary cadre of the Ministry to deputation on a very temporary basis.
This ad-hoc promotion will not entitle the officers concerned to any rights of regular promotion i.e. seniority.
The ad-hoc promotion will be for a period of 11 months from the date of joining of the officer / employee who has left on deputation or the order of promotion, whichever is earlier.

These ad-hoc promotions are being made subject to demotion of the lowest officer / staff in this order in case the post of Rat in the Under Secretary cadre is not available to the senior officers / staff on deputation in the Under Secretary cadre on their repatriation.
The ad-hoc promotion is being made subject to the final decision of the Special Leave Petition No. ID1 filed in the Supreme Court.

The ad-hoc promotion of such officers to the rank of Under Secretary is being made subject to the assumption that no departmental inquiry of any kind has been instituted against such officers as on the date of the said order. Accordingly, the department concerned should confirm and inform this department if any departmental inquiry proceedings are going on against the concerned officers.

Officers given ad-hoc promotion to the rank of Under-Secretary are required to join the post of Under-Secretary within thirty days from the date of issue of this order. Promoted aflame should be relieved within the prescribed time period by the relevant competent Hera in order to join the position of promotion.

General Administration Department, Government Decision No: SRV-2015 / Q303 / Q12, dated 12.09.2016 and General Administration Department, Government Decision No: SRV2018 / Q12, if the concerned Cell Officer refuses ad-hoc promotion to the post of Under Secretary. As per the provision in No. 159 / IAS-12, dated 01.08.2019, the names of the officers concerned will be removed from the selection list of the year 2024-25 and their eligibility for ad-hoc promotion to the post of Under Secretary will be checked on the selection list of the year 2027-28 without considering their names in the subsequent selection lists of the year 2025-26 and year 2026-27.

8. The post-promotional training as provided in the Maharashtra State Training Policy shall be binding on the concerned promoted officer or else the concerned Under-Secretary shall be demoted to the rank of Room Officer.
